    <listApp>
      <app loc="3">
        <lem source="bib:Katti+PadmanabhaSastry1995_01">śrī-<unclear>vīra</unclear>-<choice><sic><unclear>v</unclear></sic><corr>l</corr></choice><unclear>a</unclear><choice><sic><unclear>khkh</unclear></sic><corr>kṣ</corr></choice><unclear>aṇ</unclear><choice><sic>a</sic><corr>ā</corr></choice>śvame
<lb n="4" break="no"/>dha-</lem>
        <note>I have strong doubts about KPS's reading and their emendation, but have nothing better to offer.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="4">
        <lem>y<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>ā</corr></choice>jinā<unclear cert="low">m anvaye</unclear></lem>
        <rdg source="bib:Katti+PadmanabhaSastry1995_01">-y<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>ā</corr></choice>jiṇā <choice><sic>cātraya</sic><corr>kṣatriya</corr></choice>-</rdg>
        <note>Since KPM do not emend to <foreign>yājināṁ</foreign>, I suspect that the <foreign>ṇ</foreign> in their edition is a typo. I further suspect that their reading <foreign>cātraya</foreign> (which may be a misprint instead of <foreign>chātraya</foreign>) is mistaken, and the plate probably has <foreign>m anvaye</foreign> (or characters derivable through scribal error from that) at this locus.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="4">
        <lem>mahodadh<choice><sic>o</sic><corr>e</corr></choice><supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied></lem>
        <rdg source="bib:Katti+PadmanabhaSastry1995_01">mahodadh<choice><sic>o</sic><corr>ā</corr></choice></rdg>
        <note>I do not understand KPM's emendation of <foreign>mahodadho</foreign> to <foreign>mahodadhā</foreign>. It is possible that their actual reading is <foreign>mahodadhomr̥ta</foreign>, which they emend to <foreign>mahodadhāmr̥ta</foreign>, but this would still be incorrect. I believe the text, or at least the composer's intent, must have been <foreign>mahodadheḥ Amr̥ta</foreign>.</note>
      </app>
      
      
      
      
    </listApp>
